04317nam a22007575i 9780231541466DE-B159720210830012106.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||210830t20162016nyu    fo  d z      eng d  a(OCoLC)979574040  a97802315414667 a10.7312/vazq174842doi  a(DE-B1597)473091  a(OCoLC)951028385  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  anyucUS-NY 4aJA79b.V39 2017 7aPHI0400002bisacsh04a1722231 aVázquez-Arroyo, Antonio, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aPolitical Responsibility :bResponding to Predicaments of Power /cAntonio Vázquez-Arroyo. 1aNew York, NY : bColumbia University Press, c[2016] 4c©2016  a1 online resource (360 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aNew Directions in Critical Theory ;v2500tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tPreface -- tAcknowledgments -- tIntroduction -- t1. Historicizing The Ethical Turn -- t2. Responsibility in History -- t3. Autonomy, Ethics, Intrasubjectivity -- t4. Ethical Reductions -- t5. Adorno and The Dialectic of Responsibility -- t6. Political Ethic, Violence, and Defeat -- tNotes -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aScholars in the humanities and social sciences have turned to ethics to theorize politics in what seems to be an increasingly depoliticized age. Yet the move toward ethics has obscured the ongoing value of political responsibility and the vibrant life it represents as an effective response to power. Sounding the alarm for those who care about robust forms of civic engagement, this book fights for a new conception of political responsibility that meets the challenges of today's democratic practice. Antonio Y. Vázquez-Arroyo forcefully argues against the notion that modern predicaments of power can only be addressed ethically or philosophically through pristine concepts that operate outside of the political realm. By returning to the political, the individual is reintroduced to the binding principles of participatory democracy and the burdens of acting and thinking as a member of a collective. Vázquez-Arroyo historicizes the ethical turn to better understand its ascendence and reworks Adorno's dialectic of responsibility to reassert the political in contemporary thought and theory.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aGovernment accountability. 0aPolitical ethics. 0aPower (Social sciences)xMoral and ethical aspects. 0aPower (Social sciences); Moral and ethical aspects. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Movements / Critical Theory.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertColumbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311063857808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2016z9783110485301oZDB-23-DPH40uhttps://doi.org/10.7312/vazq1748440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780231541466423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780231541466.jpg  a978-3-11-063857-8  Columbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2016  aZDB-23-DPHb2016